# AI Instructions - Coding Standards & Rules

You are assisting in code modification or additions on this Astro (v5) project. Please follow these guidelines at all times.

## Directory Structure
- **UI Components**: `src/components/`
- **Layouts**: `src/layouts/` (e.g. `BaseLayout.astro`, `AdminLayout.astro`)
- **Shared Libraries**: `src/lib/`
  - `admin.ts`: Auth helper logic.
  - `db.ts`: Database row mapping and D1 SQL queries.
  - `i18n.ts`: Translation constants and localization helpers.
  - `types.ts`: Global TypeScript definitions.
  - `utils.ts`: General-purpose utilities (e.g., `formatBytes`).
- **File-based Routing**: `src/pages/`
  - Trilingual pages: `[locale]/`
  - Admin panel: `sam-admin/`
  - Admin REST API: `sam-admin/api/[...path].ts`

## Coding Standards & Conventions

### 1. Localization (i18n)
- Multi-language fields utilize the `LocalizedText` shape: `{ en: string; zhTW: string; zhCN: string }`.
- Use the translation helpers from `src/lib/i18n.ts`. Do **not** write inline ternaries:
  - **Correct**: `getLocalized(news.title, locale)`
  - **Incorrect**: `locale === "en" ? news.title.en : locale === "zh-CN" ? news.title.zhCN : news.title.zhTW`
- Use `getLocalizedVideoUrl(video, locale)` for localized video links.
- Use `localePath(locale, "/path")` to generate correct locale-aware URLs.

### 2. File Splitting & Organization
- Keep `.astro` components clean and focused on server-side rendering (SSR) and markup structure.
- **Client-Side Scripts**: If a page/component has complex client-side interactivity, extract the JavaScript into a companion file `[filename].client.ts` in the same directory.
- Link client-side scripts inside the Astro file using:
  ```html
  <script src="./filename.client.ts"></script>
  ```

### 3. Reusable Modules & Data Mapping
- Keep all SQL database query methods and row-to-model mapping functions (e.g. `mapTour`, `mapVideo`, `mapPlatform`) in `src/lib/db.ts`. Do not write raw SQL queries or mapping logic inside Astro components.
- Put general-purpose helper functions in `src/lib/utils.ts` to prevent code replication across server and client.

### 4. Admin Routing & Authentication
- Admin pages are under `src/pages/sam-admin/`.
- Auth checks are handled by middleware. Enforce proper user role restrictions (Editor vs. Owner) in `sam-admin/api/[...path].ts`.
- Database/Admin pages should set `export const prerender = false;` to support dynamic server-side rendering.

## Verification Checklist
- Run `npm run build` after any changes to verify there are no TypeScript or Astro diagnostic compilation errors.
